newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline barges softer in pre-holiday lull.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline barges softer in pre-holiday lull.

text.p: NWE gasoline markets were quiet on Tuesday with many traders away on holiday.
Prices dipped slightly with some pressure on prompt barge material but many expected demand from the U.S. to support levels after the holiday period.

"It's not surprising that prices have come off a bit. There are some people who really need to move some product but I expect the American market to open up in January and we will see even stronger prices," one large trader said.
A barge of prompt eurograde refinery material was sold by a major on Tuesday at $219 per tonne fob. Some felt prompt ARA storage material would fetch around $3 less but there were no buyers seen.
